# 🌍 Population Distribution Visualization (2022)

This project visualizes the distribution of population across countries using the *World Bank Total Population* dataset (SP.POP.TOTL). It highlights the *top 10 most populous countries in 2022* using a bar chart.

## 📊 Objective

Create a simple and effective bar chart to analyze global population distribution using real-world open data.

## 🗂 Dataset

- *Source:* [World Bank Open Data](https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SP.POP.TOTL)
- *Indicator Code:* SP.POP.TOTL
- *Format:* CSV (extracted from .zip)

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn

## 📈 Output

A bar chart showing the top 10 countries by population in 2022.

## ▶ How to Run

1. Download the dataset from the [World Bank website](https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SP.POP.TOTL)
2. Extract the ZIP and place the CSV in your project folder
3. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install pandas matplotlib seaborn